==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seta
<hw>Se"ta</hw> <pr>(s⟦emac⟧"t⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Setae</plw> <pr>(s⟦emac⟧"t⟦emac⟧)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[L. <ets>seta</ets>, <ets>saeta</ets>, a bristle.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Any slender, more or less rigid,
bristlelike organ or part; as the hairs of a caterpillar, the slender
spines of a crustacean, the hairlike processes of a protozoan, the
bristles or stiff hairs on the leaves of some plants, or the pedicel of
the capsule of a moss.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One of the movable
chitinous spines or hooks of an annelid. They usually arise in clusters
from muscular capsules, and are used in locomotion and for defense. They
are very diverse in form.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One of the spinelike
feathers at the base of the bill of certain birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Setaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
